ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

Mean response time for accurate responses to predictable B stimuli
Mean response time for accurate responses to control X stimuli
Mean accuracy of participant responses for predictive A stimuli in recognition phase

Mean accuracy of participant responses for control X stimuli in recognition phase
Mean confidence of participant responses for predictive A stimuli in recognition phase
Mean confidence of participant responses for predictable B stimuli in recognition phase
Mean confidence of participant responses for control X stimuli in recognition phase
Mean accuracy of participant responses for A probes in familiarity phase
Mean accuracy of participant responses for B probes in familiarity phase
